    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How far in advance should we book a Lake Travis party boat?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Lake Travis peak-season weekends (April\u2013September) book 6\u20138 weeks in advance \u2014 Saturdays fill fastest, especially for bachelor/bachelorette parties and corporate events. Weekdays and off-peak months (November\u2013February) are much easier, often available 2\u20133 weeks out. For milestone events we recommend 2\u20133 months lead time. Deposits hold your date: 25% if booking 14+ days out, 50% if within 14 days."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What's your weather policy for Lake Travis party boats?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Weather is never your fault, so we never charge you for it. If the captain cancels for unsafe conditions on Lake Travis, every guest gets a FREE reschedule to any future cruise, or a full refund if preferred. If weather shortens an in-progress cruise, you receive a pro-rated refund. Standard non-weather cancellations: 48-hour full-refund window after booking; after that, your deposit applies to a reschedule within 12 months. Reschedule changes 30+ days out are always free."
